      • sublist

        public static <T> List<T> sublist​(List<T> list,
                                  int from,
                                  int length)
        Returns a slice of the provided list starting with starting with element from and containing at most length elements.
        1. If from is less than zero, it is taken relative to the end of the list.
        2. If length is zero or from is past the end of the list, an empty list is returned.
        Parameters:
        list -
        from -
        length -
        Returns:
